- Yeah. So what do you think
of this munchkin?

13:22.500 --> 13:26.333
- Munchkin? I haven't heard that
for a while. I'll use that.

13:26.333 --> 13:29.333
- No, I think Em is great.

13:29.333 --> 13:31.000
- Isn't she?
Proper English girl.

13:31.000 --> 13:34.667
- So far, so good.
- It's lovely having James here.

13:34.667 --> 13:36.083
He makes me miss my family.

13:36.083 --> 13:37.833
This is a big part of my life,

13:37.833 --> 13:40.167
and I'm so glad that he's able
to share it with me.

13:40.167 --> 13:43.917
Captain Lee's upstairs,
which is very out of character.

13:43.917 --> 13:46.417
- Is there a time frame on how
long you're allowed to be here?

13:46.417 --> 13:48.000
- We have
to keep our clothes on,

13:48.000 --> 13:49.583
we're not allowed
to drink champagne,

13:49.583 --> 13:52.167
and we're not allowed
to dive off the boat.

13:52.167 --> 13:54.250
- So we can eat caviar,
just in the crew mess,

13:54.250 --> 13:55.333
and drink whiskey?

13:55.333 --> 13:57.292
- Where there's a loophole.

13:57.292 --> 13:58.917
Do you want some caviar?
- Oh, yes, Ben.

13:58.917 --> 14:00.708
- Ah, no, that's not
enough for you.

14:00.708 --> 14:02.542
- What type is that?
Is it beluga?

14:02.542 --> 14:05.042
- That's very sweet of you.
- She's very hospitable.

14:05.042 --> 14:06.708
No, it's actually
very affordable,

14:06.708 --> 14:09.167
but I've found an affordable
caviar that I like.

14:09.167 --> 14:11.042
And it doesn't kill budget.

14:11.042 --> 14:13.708
- I agreed to let Ben's brother
come and say good-bye to him.

14:13.708 --> 14:16.542
That doesn't mean, you know,
it's a two, three-hour goodbye.

14:16.542 --> 14:18.208
Could I have a word?
- Absolutely.

14:18.208 --> 14:19.500
- Thank you.

14:19.500 --> 14:21.542
But as Ben normally does,

14:21.542 --> 14:25.500
he takes everything
to the absolute limit.

14:25.500 --> 14:26.708
- Good evening.

14:26.708 --> 14:28.875
- I want him gone
and you asleep.

14:28.875 --> 14:30.625
It doesn't take an hour
to say goodbye.

14:30.625 --> 14:31.958
- Okay. Good night.
- Now.

14:31.958 --> 14:33.042
- Yeah, right now.

14:33.042 --> 14:35.375
Going by my rank
in this scenario

14:35.375 --> 14:36.792
and my rapport with Lee,

14:36.792 --> 14:39.708
I do think Lee is
treating me unfairly.

14:39.708 --> 14:42.750
He wants James off the boat,
and he wants me in bed now.

14:42.750 --> 14:45.250
- Okay, that's what I suspected.
I could tell, you know,

14:45.250 --> 14:47.583
literally in
the pressure cooker.

14:47.583 --> 14:49.250
- But when you're ordered
to go to bed

14:49.250 --> 14:53.167
by an outranking officer,
you go to bed.

14:53.167 --> 14:56.083
- You've done well with Ems.
- Love you, baby.

14:56.083 --> 14:58.500
- You know that, don't you?
- Love you too, Ben.

14:58.500 --> 15:00.917
- All right, you take care.

15:00.917 --> 15:03.292
- Good night, baby.
- Good night.

15:15.542 --> 15:17.417
- I respect Kelley
as the boatswain,

15:17.417 --> 15:18.917
and I feel bad for yelling.

15:18.917 --> 15:20.375
You know, but we don't
need to sit here

15:20.375 --> 15:22.083
and have drama
the rest of the season.

15:22.083 --> 15:24.125
We just need to get over it.

15:26.792 --> 15:28.958
- Dean is a really important
charter guest.

15:28.958 --> 15:31.792
He's polite, but he has
such high standards.

15:31.792 --> 15:33.958
- Oh.
- Just focus on the guests.

15:33.958 --> 15:36.208
This charter's
probably our most important.

15:36.208 --> 15:38.208
- Okay.

15:38.208 --> 15:40.125
- Nico has a lot of growing
to do.

15:40.125 --> 15:41.875
If he yelled at a boss
on any other boat,

15:41.875 --> 15:43.292
he'd probably be fired.

15:43.292 --> 15:45.792
But I know how valuable
he is to me.

15:45.792 --> 15:48.625
It's not worth it.

15:48.625 --> 15:50.792
- Attention all crew.
Provisions have arrived.

15:50.792 --> 15:52.583
- Copy.
If you guys could just put it

15:52.583 --> 15:54.125
on the dining table for me.

15:54.125 --> 15:55.292
- Copy.

15:55.292 --> 15:57.125
- The wall looks good.
- Yeah.

15:57.125 --> 15:58.583
- Take it for a test drive,
captain.

15:58.583 --> 16:00.125
I'll leave you in here.

16:07.167 --> 16:09.583
- Attention all crew.
We've got ten minutes

16:09.583 --> 16:10.625
until guest arrival.

16:10.625 --> 16:11.625
Over.

16:13.083 --> 16:14.958
- It's a lot of fun.

16:14.958 --> 16:16.292
- Okay, we're getting close.

16:18.333 --> 16:20.167
- All right, no shoes
for three days.

16:20.167 --> 16:21.667
- Hello.
- Hi.

16:21.667 --> 16:23.000
- Hey.
- Good to see you again.

16:23.000 --> 16:24.667
- Great to be here.
- Welcome back.

16:24.667 --> 16:25.667
So good to see you.
- Thank you.

16:25.667 --> 16:27.333
- Emily.
- Sierra.

16:27.333 --> 16:29.458
- I'm very good. How are you?
- Good. Thank you.

16:29.458 --> 16:31.167
- These guests
are absolutely gorgeous,

16:31.167 --> 16:32.833
but, you know,
they're a group of gay guys.

16:32.833 --> 16:35.333
Hi. Lauren. Nice to meet you.
Damn it.

16:35.333 --> 16:37.000
- Dean, welcome back.
- Thank you.

16:37.000 --> 16:38.792
- Always a pleasure
to have you on board.

16:38.792 --> 16:40.833
Kate will show you
around the vessel,

16:40.833 --> 16:42.500
and we'll get off the dock
and get started.

16:42.500 --> 16:44.083
- Let's do it.
- All right.

16:44.083 --> 16:45.958
Right this way, guys.
- Thanks.

16:48.875 --> 16:50.125
- Uh-huh.

16:50.125 --> 16:51.292
I'm so excited you're here.

16:51.292 --> 16:53.708
- I'm so excited to be here.

16:53.708 --> 16:55.875
- I think you'll like this boat,
just 'cause it's really open

16:55.875 --> 16:58.375
and airy and bright.

16:58.375 --> 17:00.375
This is your master suite.
- Master suite's great.

17:00.375 --> 17:02.042
- Yeah. The toilet has a remote.

17:02.042 --> 17:06.042
It opens by itself, plays music.
- So fancy.

17:06.042 --> 17:07.542
- These are our two queen rooms.

17:07.542 --> 17:10.042
- All right. Sounds good.
- Yeah.

17:10.042 --> 17:11.875
- Let's go. Bow to stern.

17:11.875 --> 17:14.000
- Once you finish calling out
distances for him,

17:14.000 --> 17:15.375
go change over into swimwear.

17:15.375 --> 17:17.708
- Okay. Copy.
- Bow's clear.

17:17.708 --> 17:20.083
- Stern line's all clear, Cap.
Stern line's all clear.

17:29.708 --> 17:30.708
- I don't like the sun.

17:30.708 --> 17:32.417
I'm gonna start wearing a burka.

17:32.417 --> 17:33.750
- Are you ready for us?

17:33.750 --> 17:35.500
Napkins in laps, come on, guys.

17:38.417 --> 17:40.583
- Ben, so we're about
to turn a corner. Are you okay?

17:40.583 --> 17:43.417
- No. I just spilled
f---ing egg yolk everywhere.

17:43.417 --> 17:46.083
I'm a little nervous
going into this first meal.

17:46.083 --> 17:48.917
We have a history
of nervousness together.

17:48.917 --> 17:51.417
- There is plastic on my food!

17:51.417 --> 17:53.333
- We need to make them
another dish.

17:53.333 --> 17:54.583
- Either way,
the chef should be fired.

17:54.583 --> 17:55.583
- Yeah.

17:55.583 --> 17:58.167
- Every meal has to be perfect.

18:04.500 --> 18:06.667
- Do you mind if I put
the spoon in it already?

18:06.667 --> 18:08.000
- Yeah, I'll try and do it,

18:08.000 --> 18:10.250
because I'd rather avoid
the caviar.

18:10.250 --> 18:13.958
- Ben has a very sensitive
relationship with Dean,

18:13.958 --> 18:17.083
because Dean's the one person
that holds him accountable.

18:17.083 --> 18:19.292
So right here have
just an amuse.

18:19.292 --> 18:22.917
It's egg salad
with bowfin caviar. Enjoy.

18:22.917 --> 18:24.625
- So, it's basically eggs
with eggs.

18:24.625 --> 18:26.375
- Heck, yeah.
- Eggs with eggs.

18:28.292 --> 18:30.125
- Kate, how are they?

18:30.125 --> 18:31.958
Did they like the caviar thing?

18:31.958 --> 18:34.583
- Dean was very funny. He said,
"Oh, it's eggs with eggs."

18:34.583 --> 18:37.458
- What does that mean?

18:37.458 --> 18:38.958
- A tragic story.

18:40.417 --> 18:42.958
- Look at his--
send it back.

18:46.250 --> 18:48.792
- Watch the bow, please.
God damn it!

18:48.792 --> 18:50.125
I expected us
to be further along

18:50.125 --> 18:51.458
this far into the season.

18:51.458 --> 18:53.708
I'm gonna make
some alterations.

18:57.708 --> 18:58.542
- Have you finished, then?

18:58.208 --> 18:58.542
- Yeah, I'm done.

19:01.167 --> 19:03.167
- Can you imagine life
without butter?

19:03.167 --> 19:05.167
That would be harsh.

19:05.167 --> 19:06.167
Brilliant.

19:06.167 --> 19:07.333
The chef position,

19:07.333 --> 19:09.000
out of every position,

19:09.000 --> 19:11.500
you know, our time frames are
really tough.

19:11.500 --> 19:12.917
We have too much to do.

19:12.917 --> 19:16.500
I dare you to walk a day
in my shoes.

19:16.500 --> 19:19.458
- Ooh.
- First we have airline chicken

19:19.458 --> 19:21.500
with an apple
whole-grain coleslaw.

19:21.500 --> 19:23.083
- Sounds good. Thank you.

19:25.917 --> 19:28.833
- Is Dean seeming to be happy?
- He hasn't talked.

19:28.833 --> 19:30.792
He was just busy chewing.
- F---.

19:30.792 --> 19:32.500
- Kelley, Kelley, Lee.
- Go for Kelley.

19:32.500 --> 19:34.875
- Now would be a good time
for the toys and the slide.

19:34.875 --> 19:36.083
- Roger that.

19:40.875 --> 19:43.208
- Tonight we're doing
Chinese New Year party.

19:43.208 --> 19:44.708
Are you interested
at all in doing,

19:44.708 --> 19:46.875
like, a Chinese cuisine?

19:46.875 --> 19:48.542
- Yeah.

19:48.542 --> 19:50.375
- Kate? Is Chef Ben busy?
Is he still working?

19:50.375 --> 19:52.708
- No.
- I would like to speak to him.

19:52.708 --> 19:54.375
- Hey, Ben.
Dean's in the main salon,

19:54.375 --> 19:56.875
would love to chat with you.

19:56.875 --> 19:59.500
- Sure.
- Ben, how are you?

19:59.500 --> 20:00.708
- Hey.
- I wasn't thrilled to see you

20:00.708 --> 20:02.625
when I got on board.

20:02.625 --> 20:04.375
- I'm sorry, Dean,
but I'm not that thrilled

20:04.375 --> 20:07.708
to see you either, so.

20:07.708 --> 20:09.208
- Lunch--

20:09.208 --> 20:11.708
it was amazing.
- Oh, well, thank you.

20:11.708 --> 20:14.542
- And so I want to apologize
for doubting you at all.

20:14.542 --> 20:16.500
Everything was so good.
- Oh, good, cool.

20:16.500 --> 20:18.583
- So now you've really got a lot
to live up to now,

20:18.583 --> 20:20.333
because the first meal you do
is just--

20:20.333 --> 20:21.833
- That's not very fair, though.
Now, I'm kidding.

20:21.833 --> 20:23.000
- No, I'm not fair,
I'm never fair.

20:23.000 --> 20:24.583
- I'm joking, I'm joking.

20:24.583 --> 20:26.583
I set the bar high,
and he expects me

20:26.583 --> 20:28.167
to keep it that high.

20:28.167 --> 20:29.750
It's Dean's world,

20:29.750 --> 20:31.417
and we're just lucky
to be living in it.

20:31.417 --> 20:34.333
- You made my day. Thank you.
- You're welcome.

20:34.333 --> 20:35.750
- Oh, I love that there's
no women

20:35.750 --> 20:38.750
and no lipstick
to scrub off the glasses.

20:38.750 --> 20:40.042
- Mm-hmm. That's so funny.

20:40.042 --> 20:41.542
- Hey, Emily?
- Yeah?

20:41.542 --> 20:43.500
- Listen, I would like
to take my break now,

20:43.500 --> 20:45.833
so clear up lunch, stay
kind of on guest service...

20:45.833 --> 20:47.000
- Yeah.
- And I'll be back.

20:47.000 --> 20:48.333
- Okay.

20:48.333 --> 20:50.375
- The little things, eh?
- I know.

20:52.542 --> 20:53.833
- Whoo!

20:55.208 --> 20:56.667
- Oh!

20:58.292 --> 21:12.083
- I totally get
how dolphins feel.

21:12.083 --> 21:13.292
- Th

21:13.292 --> 21:15.458
is going on around here?

21:15.458 --> 21:18.958
- Can we get some service out
here on the aft deck, please?

21:18.958 --> 21:20.583
- They don't make them
like they used to.

21:20.583 --> 21:22.250
- No, they do not.

21:23.792 --> 21:27.292
- Kate, Kate, Lee.
- Copy.

21:27.292 --> 21:28.792
- Can I trust anyone?

21:32.875 --> 21:34.958
- I can't even leave
for five minutes

21:34.958 --> 21:38.292
before our boss is calling
for service

21:38.292 --> 21:43.167
for our most high-maintenance
charter guest.

21:43.167 --> 21:44.583
- Can I just do
a skinny girl margarita?

21:44.583 --> 21:46.083
- Yeah.
It's completely unfair,

21:46.083 --> 21:48.167
and I don't have time
to worry about it,

21:48.167 --> 21:49.667
so I'll just do the work myself.

21:49.667 --> 21:51.167
Will one of you please
go get the blender

21:51.167 --> 21:52.667
from the pantry upstairs?

21:52.667 --> 21:54.000
- I'll grab it.

21:54.000 --> 21:56.167
- Work it. Smile.
- There you go.

21:56.167 --> 21:57.917
There you go. One more.
- There you go.

21:57.917 --> 22:00.167
- Kelley, I need you to go
pick up a load of fireworks.

22:00.167 --> 22:01.958
- Roger. En route.
- Kelley?

22:01.958 --> 22:03.417
Can you pick up the flowers

22:03.417 --> 22:04.625
I ordered for Emily
while you're out?

22:04.625 --> 22:06.083
- Yeah.

22:12.917 --> 22:14.417
- Okay, let's go ahead
and bring this up,

22:14.417 --> 22:15.833
'cause it's 5:31.

22:15.833 --> 22:17.083
- All right.

22:17.083 --> 22:19.167
- Hi, guys.
- Hello.

22:19.167 --> 22:20.500
- I like a little bit
of charcuterie.

22:20.500 --> 22:22.458
- Oh, hummus.
- Excellent.

22:22.458 --> 22:25.000
- Cheers, everyone.
- Cheers.

22:29.208 --> 22:31.042
- I wish I could take
a break, but I can't.

22:31.042 --> 22:34.042
Captain Lee's calling me
the moment I go on break

22:34.042 --> 22:35.208
for service.

22:35.208 --> 22:37.375
I know, baby, I know.

22:37.375 --> 22:39.042
- Yeah. You don't know.

22:39.042 --> 22:41.042
Your girlfriend, like,
you distract her too much

22:41.042 --> 22:42.208
or something.

22:42.208 --> 22:43.958
- What?
- I am disappointed,

22:43.958 --> 22:47.542
because I told Emily
stay on service.

22:47.542 --> 22:49.833
- Do you expect her
to just stand in front of them

22:49.833 --> 22:51.125
all day long?

22:51.125 --> 22:53.042
Is that what service is
on a yacht?

22:53.042 --> 22:57.542
Hands down, Emily is the best
second stew Kate's ever had.

22:57.542 --> 23:00.500
She basically runs
the whole boat.

23:00.500 --> 23:02.542
- You know, Ben, if you weren't
romantically involved

23:02.542 --> 23:04.417
with Emily, I don't think
you would get involved

23:04.417 --> 23:06.583
with the interior workings.

23:06.583 --> 23:08.417
- You're blaming me
at the same time.

23:08.417 --> 23:10.042
- I'm not blaming anyone.

23:10.042 --> 23:12.375
- It sounded a lot like you were
blaming me and Ems.

23:15.042 --> 23:16.583
- Just give her the flowers.
You stay out.

23:16.583 --> 23:18.083
I've got to get off this dock.

23:18.083 --> 23:20.250
All right, just set them
right here next to me.

23:20.250 --> 23:22.375
- Those don't look
like fireworks, Kelley.

23:22.375 --> 23:24.250
- No, they don't.

23:24.250 --> 23:26.917
- Be sure you fill me in when
you get back on what they are.

23:26.917 --> 23:30.542
- Emily, happy birthday.
But Ben, what the f---?

23:31.667 --> 23:33.750
- Watch the bow, please.

23:33.750 --> 23:35.750
God damn it!

23:35.750 --> 23:39.750
Did you not hear me when
I said watch the bow, please?

23:39.750 --> 23:42.083
Obviously not.
F---.

23:42.083 --> 23:44.917
- Flowers.
Don't let Emily see those.

23:44.917 --> 23:46.250
It's heavy.

23:53.625 --> 23:56.542
- I'm always trying to one-up
myself to surprise Dean.

23:56.542 --> 23:58.958
So I'm gonna try and push
my creative boundaries

23:58.958 --> 24:01.333
with tonight's
Chinese New Year-themed dinner.

24:03.750 --> 24:05.958
- Hello, you.
- Hello.

24:05.958 --> 24:09.083
- We're gonna get loose, baby.
Ugh!

24:09.083 --> 24:10.708
- Hey, Emily?

24:10.708 --> 24:13.417
The Chinese New Year party is
kind of a big deal.

24:13.417 --> 24:14.708
I have to focus.

24:14.708 --> 24:16.125
So if you'll just run up
to the bow

24:16.125 --> 24:17.792
and see if the guests are okay
real quick.

24:17.792 --> 24:19.958
- Yeah. Okay, I'll be quick.

24:21.625 --> 24:23.750
- Kelley, come on up
to the wheelhouse.

24:23.750 --> 24:25.583
- Roger that.
I'm on my way up now.

24:30.417 --> 24:33.333
- Who the f--- died?
- Nobody.

24:33.333 --> 24:36.000
Ben got those for Emily
for her birthday tomorrow.

24:36.000 --> 24:37.417
- Well, I could give
a flying sh--

24:37.417 --> 24:39.000
about the goddamn flowers.

24:39.000 --> 24:41.000
We're on charter.
I expected us to be

24:41.000 --> 24:44.333
further along
this far into the season.

24:44.333 --> 24:47.167
He's got the fireworks.
He's got a big vase of flowers.

24:47.167 --> 24:49.333
And then he smacks the boat
with the tender.

24:49.333 --> 24:51.833
I mean, he's just everywhere.
I don't know what he's thinking.

24:51.833 --> 24:54.833
I think I'm gonna make
some alterations.

24:54.833 --> 24:56.417
Let me think on it.

24:56.417 --> 24:58.833
- Sounds good.
- Kelley was given a second shot

24:58.833 --> 25:01.833
at redemption, but I haven't
seen any improvement.

25:01.833 --> 25:03.542
Something's got to happen.

25:07.000 --> 25:09.708
- Can I get a deckhand to help
me out in the galley, please?

25:09.708 --> 25:11.625
- Copy.

25:11.625 --> 25:13.292
- Kate's been, like,
putting me on things

25:13.292 --> 25:15.333
that she wouldn't usually,
and stopping me midway

25:15.333 --> 25:16.375
and then going,
"No, now do this.

25:16.375 --> 25:17.667
No, now do this."

25:17.667 --> 25:18.875
Like I feel like
I'm annoying her.

25:18.875 --> 25:20.083
- Yeah.

25:21.708 --> 25:23.833
- You think it's because of Ben?
- Yeah.

25:23.833 --> 25:25.333
- Have you talked
to Ben about it?

25:25.333 --> 25:27.042
- No, I'm going to.
I'm gonna ask.

25:27.042 --> 25:28.542
- You should.

25:31.375 --> 25:34.500
- Daddy's here.
- Oh, good.

25:36.708 --> 25:38.875
- It may be a hard time
to, like, ask or whatever,

25:38.875 --> 25:40.458
like, 'cause I know
we're really busy,

25:40.458 --> 25:42.542
but are you okay
with everything with me?

25:42.542 --> 25:44.125
- Why do you ask?

25:44.125 --> 25:46.042
- 'Cause earlier I felt
like maybe you were

25:46.042 --> 25:47.542
getting annoyed with me,
and I just wanted to--

25:47.542 --> 25:50.167
- I was frustrated
that Captain had to call

25:50.167 --> 25:52.333
over the radio for service.

25:52.333 --> 25:55.542
That's why I came back up,
and it was fine.

25:55.542 --> 25:57.000
- Okay.

26:09.333 --> 26:10.542
- Guys, you want to come out
to dinner?

26:10.542 --> 26:11.667
- Yeah.
- We're gonna celebrate

26:11.667 --> 26:13.250
Year of the Dog today.
- Yeah.

26:13.250 --> 26:16.542
- A little Chinese New Year
celebration.

26:16.542 --> 26:18.083
- Good job, Nico.
- They're ready.

26:18.083 --> 26:20.583
- Soft shell crab,
and avocado, corn.

26:20.583 --> 26:23.750
